{"insight":"Time Lives Where Memory, Attention, and Hope Meet","publicTitle":"When Grief Breaks Time","plainSummary":"Grief can break time by scattering memory, attention, and hope until life feels unable to move.","atAGlance":"Pain can make a day stop moving. The past becomes hard to hold, the present becomes hard to meet, and the future becomes hard to imagine. Healing may begin by gently rejoining these three powers. The test is whether time returns as they return.","keyPoints":["Meaning fails when memory, attention, and hope fall apart.","The risk is mistaking broken time for personal weakness.","Watch whether small future plans help time feel livable again."],"match":["grief stops time"],"tags":["grief","time","healing","trauma"]}
